Cell[CellGroupData[{

Cell[TextData[StyleBox["Abstract",
 FontWeight->"Bold"]], "Section",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.922530634139595*^9, 
  3.92253063601688*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"8f73890f-0d6e-4057-b374-\
33794ae9113d"],

Cell["\<\
We compare two numerical solutions for the free motion of a spinning, \
symmetrical top. One solution is by the standard method of integrating \
differential equations, discretizing the independent time variable as late as \
possible in the solution process. The other solution begins by discretizing \
the dynamical variables and the Lagrangian as early as possible in the \
solution process, then solving derived algebraic recurrences by root-finding. \
\>", "Text",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.946241217570574*^9, 3.9462413530510283`*^9}, {
   3.946241404598276*^9, 3.946241451311286*^9}, {3.946241534254261*^9, 
   3.9462416471263933`*^9}, {3.946241678549583*^9, 3.946241806217373*^9}, {
   3.946242059576055*^9, 3.946242068839816*^9}, 3.946285039444363*^9, {
   3.94628534459074*^9, 3.94628535420503*^9}, {3.946285385925694*^9, 
   3.946285413979114*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"299e0c16-8362-4b6a-bd04-\
510ebe8821d3"],

Cell["\<\
Our contribution is to find that the early-discretized solution has no \
secular, long-term drift in conserved quantities (energy and momenta), unlike \
the standard, late-discretized solution, which exhibits small but steady \
drifts in the sixth or seventh significant figure. \
\>", "Text",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.946241217570574*^9, 3.9462413530510283`*^9}, {
  3.946241404598276*^9, 3.946241451311286*^9}, {3.946241534254261*^9, 
  3.9462416471263933`*^9}, {3.946241678549583*^9, 3.946241806217373*^9}, {
  3.946242059576055*^9, 
  3.946242068839816*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"341ca153-6174-46ed-b3b6-\
6906c61f68d8"],

Cell["\<\
While the early-discretized solution has no secular drifts, its conserved \
quantities have oscillatory noise in the fourth or fifth significant figure, \
about 2000 times larger in amplitude than the drift in the standard solution. \
Considering its other benefits\[LongDash]ease of implementation and tuning\
\[LongDash]we find that the discrete method is worth further study and \
optimization.\
\>", "Text",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.946241217570574*^9, 3.9462413530510283`*^9}, {
  3.946241404598276*^9, 3.946241451311286*^9}, {3.946241534254261*^9, 
  3.9462416471263933`*^9}, {3.946241678549583*^9, 3.946241875136814*^9}, {
  3.946241928512844*^9, 3.946241940867689*^9}, {3.94624197455068*^9, 
  3.9462419933272543`*^9}, {3.9462420274601583`*^9, 3.94624209270048*^9}, {
  3.946285062727325*^9, 
  3.94628519142339*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"1fda2ccb-4c49-4d89-ad3d-\
e7262cfca8b3"]
}, Open  ]],

Cell[CellGroupData[{

Cell[TextData[StyleBox["Introduction",
 FontWeight->"Bold"]], "Section",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.944663505958761*^9, 
  3.944663507759389*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"0263c2be-8bf8-488f-8f87-\
553c41205779"],

Cell[TextData[{
 "Traditionally, one solves problems in classical mechanics via differential \
equations of motion, discretized for numerical solution as last as possible \
in the solution process. We call this tactic ",
 StyleBox["late discretization",
  FontWeight->"Bold",
  FontSlant->"Italic"],
 ". By contrast, one can discretize the dynamical variables and the \
Lagrangian at the outset and avoid differential equations and their numerical \
methods altogether. We call this tactic ",
 StyleBox["early discretization",
  FontWeight->"Bold",
  FontSlant->"Italic"],
 ". The resulting equations of motion are algebraic, solved by iterated \
root-finding. Theoretically, at least, the early-discretized methods conserve \
energy and momenta by \
construction.[1,\[NonBreakingSpace]2,\[NonBreakingSpace]3]"
}], "Text",
 CellChangeTimes->CompressedData["
1:eJxTTMoPSmViYGCQAGIQrZLzned88lvH+fOW6YFoq6zHniCau1rdB0T/cYsK
ANFZey9mgPlcSrkgWiPlUA2IftC7sBFEL5T/2w6ij/W4zwDRXPxP5oBoE/sd
m0C00XW5LSBaTqrZ9wKQ3nJ1PZgOWrEhBERrCXSHguh9cuV2N4B038HlHiBa
/L+yL4hWyP7tB6KfnX2UBKL3+HikgOgX2dtyQfQh7kUtIHoXf14PiN7sZN0H
om2WHp4Kor9cNpkGovUuP98IotsK/20C0RYdNttB9IFWn50g2uuA+X4QPWX5
yRMg2qlVzvYmkA4un2MPooVqHPJuA2lhmagiEB0b2L+mJ+Wt48emoO0g2uVM
B/udtLeOdW8vCIJo9Zf/VUH0vCMKWiB67nw74Y9A+tkXG0UQDQDXMtEz
  "],ExpressionUUID->"3a1edfe0-476f-4a8a-883e-6a76b65c3190"],

Cell["\<\
Numerical methods for differential equations comprise a vast variety of \
algorithms, sensitive to multiple tuning parameters. Bringing a solution to \
ground can be an expensive process of trial-and-error and compromises. By \
contrast, discrete methods have only one tuning parameter\[LongDash]the time \
step.\
\>", "Text",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.9446426637319508`*^9, 3.944642933206863*^9}, {
  3.944643151106717*^9, 3.94464316923377*^9}, {3.944643202821165*^9, 
  3.944643398554372*^9}, {3.944643433063841*^9, 3.944643558074726*^9}, {
  3.9446435970485687`*^9, 3.944643647910111*^9}, {3.9446437782359343`*^9, 
  3.944643815126836*^9}, {3.944643989757715*^9, 3.944644000963769*^9}, {
  3.944645228096938*^9, 3.944645229494837*^9}, {3.944645285520547*^9, 
  3.944645292345723*^9}, {3.9446614917225027`*^9, 3.9446615732423773`*^9}, {
  3.944661609124889*^9, 3.944661623856827*^9}, {3.944661783087634*^9, 
  3.944661794259367*^9}, {3.944661869700672*^9, 3.944661952241003*^9}, {
  3.9446626129397497`*^9, 3.944662626604862*^9}, {3.944663588003296*^9, 
  3.94466359938002*^9}, {3.945031229033833*^9, 3.945031246545381*^9}, {
  3.946242285102981*^9, 
  3.946242287039089*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"bf1d62cc-1cfb-44f2-ab08-\
a2f5b8bc5992"],

Cell["\<\
In this notebook, we contrast a traditional numerical solution for the \
symmetrical top with a new discrete solution. The two solutions match to \
three significant figures: within the width of a plotting line. The \
traditional solution exhibits secular drift in conserved energy and momenta. \
While small\[LongDash]in the sixth or seventh significant \
figure\[LongDash]the poor conservation will eventually become noticeable, \
requiring a \[OpenCurlyDoubleQuote]reboot.\[CloseCurlyDoubleQuote]. By \
contrast, the discrete solution exhibits only stable oscillatory error in the \
conserved quantities. While larger\[LongDash]in the fourth or fifth decimal \
place\[LongDash]these errors are not noticeable, mostly because they are \
stable in the long run.\
\>", "Text",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.944662737674515*^9, 3.944662775328148*^9}, {
  3.944662807377158*^9, 3.9446628743864117`*^9}, {3.9446636687388077`*^9, 
  3.944663803452661*^9}, {3.944663931211588*^9, 3.944663992265367*^9}, {
  3.9446678653786182`*^9, 3.944667921344223*^9}, {3.944668103961116*^9, 
  3.944668139757341*^9}, {3.9450312722198963`*^9, 3.945031301982358*^9}, {
  3.9462423101116667`*^9, 3.946242323832954*^9}, {3.946242424329072*^9, 
  3.946242450392848*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"3c6ecde2-22cb-4c40-9fe7-\
eefca04c6545"],

Cell["\<\
The contribution of this notebook is applying discrete dynamics to this \
problem from scratch. While we have seen theoretical discrete dynamics for \
the top,[9] we have not seen a convincing numerical demonstration. The theory \
leaves us unsatisfied that the method can be effectively implemented, let \
alone easily. Here, we show that it can be both.\
\>", "Text",
 CellChangeTimes->CompressedData["
1:eJxTTMoPSmViYGAQAWIQffDzgUPLk986vq63PgGieWcInQHRp8O/vAHRL/oN
foLok3L7mVcAaT+5DjUQPWnaby0Q3aPzwxhEr5ATDAPRgg8ZokC0yf/aShB9
77+82EogLZahqQui3/xKLwTRCpcrakB0vcjzBhDdZHelDURH8B7bAaK7vpmf
B9HTWBffANFfcjLug2jzI7pSO4F0evANMJ11Qcp8F5C2masJpleZizqC6EWB
Fc4g+ob0yxQQ3ccZmQ6i027tTN4DpHfUK6WA6OrT2g7ngDRTmqIriD7NvHvP
eSAdbqh7AERPCd9Ydxtkj9KxehAtsOH91Z6Ut44hJg53QDQAzAmn5A==
  "],ExpressionUUID->"2c72d729-4fe3-4d5d-b033-0e5a23bc2417"],

Cell["\<\
Despite these demonstrable benefits, the discrete implementation in this \
notebook is too slow. However, with this and our prior successes with \
discrete harmonic oscillators,[7,\[NonBreakingSpace]8] we are convinced that \
the natural benefits of discrete dynamics justify further study and \
optimization. \
\>", "Text",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.944566409876808*^9, 3.944566440668721*^9}, {
   3.944566538002133*^9, 3.9445666576229057`*^9}, {3.944577470358176*^9, 
   3.944577519332995*^9}, {3.9445775631642838`*^9, 3.944577569000798*^9}, {
   3.944577630319983*^9, 3.944577678519432*^9}, {3.94460004272836*^9, 
   3.944600045577806*^9}, 3.9446001308330584`*^9, {3.944604456581972*^9, 
   3.9446044587760363`*^9}, {3.944641075593165*^9, 3.944641091715166*^9}, {
   3.9446441242811003`*^9, 3.944644130287098*^9}, {3.944645406081489*^9, 
   3.944645424520063*^9}, {3.946242494360449*^9, 
   3.9462424993284407`*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"6e454b2c-2fbe-4351-a15a-\
ce84163af313"]
}, Open  ]],

