Cell["\<\
Mathematica has no trouble, numerically, with these equations, given \
plausible initial conditions. There is a great deal of automation hidden in \
this call: automatic (and opaque) choice of algorithm, time step, and values \
for various tuning parameters. If we were writing an integrator from scratch, \
we would have much work to do. \
\>", "Text",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.925153110848729*^9, 3.925153143673761*^9}, {
   3.925154592535503*^9, 3.925154593968121*^9}, {3.925161540346029*^9, 
   3.925161563699177*^9}, {3.94406580590751*^9, 3.944065831948279*^9}, 
   3.94440147129144*^9, {3.944601757681028*^9, 3.9446018497526693`*^9}, {
